{# gml/bind-effector.j2 - KnowAct: analogy, infer, abduct, bind #}
{# Purpose: Apply effector to port, infer state-shift #}

{% from 'gml/validate-inputs.j2' import validate_concept, validate_effectors %}
{% from 'gml/regulation-instrument.j2' import start_span, end_span, record_error, audit_log %}
{% from 'gml/macros.j2' import mwc_state_function, hill_coefficient, partition_function %}

{% set concept = inputs.concept %}
{% set effectors = inputs.effectors %}

{# Regulation span start #}
{{ start_span('bind', concept.id | default('unknown')) }}

{# Validate inputs #}
{% set concept_errors = validate_concept(concept) %}
{% set effector_errors = validate_effectors(effectors) %}

{% if concept_errors and concept_errors | length > 0 %}
{{ record_error('bind', 'GML_INVALID_CONCEPT', concept_errors | join('; ')) }}
{% include 'gml/error-validation.j2' %}
{{ end_span('bind', 'error', {'errors': concept_errors | length}) }}
{% elif effector_errors and effector_errors | length > 0 %}
{{ record_error('bind', 'GML_INVALID_EFFECTOR', effector_errors | join('; ')) }}
{% include 'gml/error-validation.j2' %}
{{ end_span('bind', 'error', {'errors': effector_errors | length}) }}
{% else %}

{% set compatible_ports = [] %}
{% for effector in effectors %}
{% for port in concept.ports %}
{% if port.effector_shape == effector.shape %}
{% set _ = compatible_ports.append({'effector': effector, 'port': port}) %}
{% endif %}
{% endfor %}
{% endfor %}

**Compatible bindings identified:**

{% for binding in compatible_ports %}
- {{ binding.effector.name }} → {{ binding.port.name }} (c = {{ binding.port.affinity_c }})
{% endfor %}

### Equilibrium Shift Prediction

{% set old_alpha = concept.current_alpha %}
{% set new_alpha = old_alpha + (effectors | sum(attribute='concentration')) %}
{% set n = concept.ports | length %}
{% set c_avg = (concept.ports | sum(attribute='affinity_c')) / n if n > 0 else 1.0 %}
{% set L = concept.l %}

{% set old_r_bar = mwc_state_function(concept.l, c_avg, n, old_alpha) %}
{% set new_r_bar = mwc_state_function(concept.l, c_avg, n, new_alpha) %}

| Parameter | Before | After | Δ |
|-----------|--------|-------|---|
| α (contextual pressure) | {{ old_alpha | round(3) }} | {{ new_alpha | round(3) }} | {{ (new_alpha - old_alpha) | round(3) }} |
| R̄ (progressive probability) | {{ (old_r_bar * 100) | round(1) }}% | {{ (new_r_bar * 100) | round(1) }}% | {{ ((new_r_bar - old_r_bar) * 100) | round(1) }}% |

{% if new_r_bar > old_r_bar %}
**Interpretation:** The effector(s) shift the concept toward **progressive/open** interpretation.
{% elif new_r_bar < old_r_bar %}
**Interpretation:** The effector(s) shift the concept toward **conservative/closed** interpretation.
{% else %}
**Interpretation:** The effector(s) produce **no net shift** in interpretive equilibrium.
{% endif %}

### Binding Analogy

{% if compatible_ports | length > 0 %}
{% set binding = compatible_ports[0] %}
{% if binding.port.affinity_c < 1 %}
Like oxygen binding to hemoglobin, {{ binding.effector.name }} binds with higher affinity to the R-state,
stabilizing the progressive interpretation and shifting the conformational equilibrium.
{% elif binding.port.affinity_c > 1 %}
Like 2,3-BPG binding to hemoglobin, {{ binding.effector.name }} binds with higher affinity to the T-state,
stabilizing the conservative interpretation and reducing access to the progressive frame.
{% else %}
Like a neutral ligand, {{ binding.effector.name }} binds without strong state preference,
shifting equilibrium through concentration rather than selectivity.
{% endif %}
{% endif %}

{# Audit log #}
{{ audit_log('bind', concept.id, old_r_bar, new_r_bar, 'success') }}
{{ end_span('bind', 'success', {'delta_r_bar': new_r_bar - old_r_bar}) }}
{% endif %}
